headline: Markets Are Betting on a Flurry of Rate Cuts. They’re Often Wrong.
summary: Financial markets are betting the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates several times over the next few months.  It’s well understood that the Federal Reserve will lower its benchmark interest rate at its Sept. 16-17 meeting.  Fed Chair Jerome Powell gave a strong signal at last week’s Jackson Hole event, saying that the central bank could soon adjust its policy stance.
